Program: Outlook
Title: 29/12/2009
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p005hzs8
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 30 Dec 2009
Forgiveness and Reconciliation In this programme we hear the stories of people who despite huge personal trauma are using the language of peace and understanding to ease not just their own pain but also that of others Park Chun Hwan and Im Bong Taek tell their story of torture, betrayal and reconciliation in South Korea. Patrick Magee, a former IRA bomber and Jo Berry the daughter of one of the men he killed who are now firm friends Also Israel Rami Elhanan and Palestinian Bassam Aramin who have both lost daughters in the conflict tell us why they're united in working for peace. And the Reverend Ruth Scott discusses forgiveness and reconciliation with Matthew. Show less